metadata.name: FairyCells II #63
metadata.description:
FairyCells II is intended as a logical continuation of the first FairyCells series. By dropping the plotter drawing constraint, new perspectives for exploration appeared.
This is how these cells began to intertwine, live together, mutate and change color, like an evolving system.

What surprises me the most in this new series, is the stories appearing behind each new composition. See how these abstracts shapes can come to life and narrate us things through our imagination.

Each color palette takes us into a different world, drawing a very specific atmosphere.

As me, let yourself be carried away by these stories 💫 !

Artwork by Julien_Espagnon, 2022.

Control : Press « S » to save the image as a PNG.

metadata.name: Tails of Majestic Creatures #1
metadata.description:
Excerpt from the Annuls of WorSAGE (the Worshipful Society of Adventurers and Generative Explorers) XXVII.Vol.2048

"Some of the fantastically colored reeds that grow in clumps along the banks of the Tezonian river have profoundly affected the local inhabitants' culture, and beliefs.

Legend tells of how there lived majestic creatures, that were so beautiful, and dazzling, that they greatly offended Nocturna - the Deity of the Night. After many unsuccessful attempts to get rid of them, usually foiled by the clever Majestic Creatures in elaborate ways, Nocturna cast a powerful spell upon them. This spell was extremely effective and made the Majestic Creatures plummet, with great speed, into the ground leaving only their tails to show.

The creatures then turned their energy to nature, and joined as one to become a deity of the natural world. They rise, and protect creatures from harm, especially during the night.

The reeds (tails) are held as sacred, and believed to have healing powers.

I have created this graphical study of the tails (exotic reeds) for your informational requirements and ocular interest.

128 images are planned to follow henceforth, subject to available minters."

s will save a 4000x4000 jpg of the image. 
g will convert to gray.
c will convert back to color.
m will save a 4000x4000 monochrome jpg of the image.

Coded in P5.js

metadata.name: Lakes and Mountains Ink Painting #31
metadata.description:
Ink wash painting is a type of Chinese ink brush painting which uses black ink, such as that used in Chinese calligraphy, in different concentrations.
In landscape painting the scenes depicted are typically imaginary, or very loose adaptations of actual views.
-
All made with p5js

objkt.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I. #49

metadata.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I. #49
metadata.description:
Experimental generative collection that merges analog photography, AI, generative text, and algorithmic coding, by digging down into the essence and building blocks of the different artistic communication channels. 

This work engages with all aforementioned mediums in a joint manner, guided by a random process. It starts with a collection of analog photographs, shot on film and scanned that were later used as a training dataset in Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) training. This way, A.I. learns the main characteristics of film photography. In particular, it mimics its recognizable grain. Another type of pixel grain is added with the use of code and pixel shifting as well as digital manipulation. Finally, the last type of “grain” appears with the use of generative text where a different kind of A.I. was given a short description of the project and instructed to imagine the rest of the story. The fragmented and void of meaning parts of generative text are added to the images as one of the possible traits.

issuer.name: Study of atom in analog, digital and A.I.
